If your reading this, you probably dont know all the options this mod provides. This is here to change that.



||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||

Section One : Vanilla Modifications

[Is Contaminable]
- Allows or Disallows the useage of contamination on Humans. | Is not mod reliant

[Resist Scream]
- Human doesn't care for screams. Does not set off "On Screamed" signals | Is not mod reliant

[GrabbedOnAttack]
- Human can be grabbed by zombies. | Is not mod reliant

[InvincebleOnAttack]
- Turns human invincble on attack, Chance of bugging. | Is not mod reliant

[AllowMultipleAttackers]
- Lets multiple zombies attack | Is not mod reliant

[VisionFollowTarget]
- Sniper aim/lasers do not chase enemies. | Is not mod reliant

[FleeBeforeZombieExplode]
- Humans run from explosions. | Is not mod reliant

[IgnoreDamage]
- Humans don't notice getting hurt. | Is not mod reliant

[Attitude] | Is not mod reliant
- Fearful, Makes Human act like a civilian.
- Neutral, Human will not chase zombies, Waits for zombie to come to them.
- Aggressive, Human will chase zombies.
- Ignore, Self explanitory.

[RelayAlertOverTime] | Is not mod reliant
- Human can alert other humans.

[AlertRelayRadius] | Is not mod reliant
- How far away Human can alert other Humans.

[AlertRelayRatio] | Is not mod reliant
- Bigger number means more people can be chain-alerted, smaller means less.

[Cornered] | Is not mod reliant
- Supposed to make human act like its cornered, dont know if it actually works tho lmao.

||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||

Section Two : Modded Modifications

| Combat

[HitsMultipleTargets]
- Human can hit multiple targets at once.

[Max Targets]
- How many tagets can be hit at once.

[NextTargetHitMultiplier]
- How much less/more damage is dealt to the enemy behind the intended target.

[Attack Frequency]
- How fast the Human attacks.

[Damage]
- How much damage the Human deals.

[DamageType]
- What type of damage is dealt

[Aim Range]
- How far a Human will prepare to attack.

[Attack Range]
- How far a Human will start attacking.

[Damage Range]
- How far a Human attack will deal damage.

| Misc

[MoveSpeeds]
- Sprint Speed.
- Run Speed (Humans use this when chasing enemys).
- Walk Speed.

[MaximumFallHeight] | Obsolete
- This is obsolete, use FallVelocity instead. 

[FallVelocityThreshold]
- How fast a Human needs to go to die from fall damage.

[Voice]
- The voice the Human uses for dialog.

[Vision]
- How far away the Human can see enemies from.

[Health]
- Sets Humans health.

[Is Invincible]
- Sets Human invincible.

[Is Stealthy]
- Humans wont be targeted by zombies.


||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
Section Three : Other Editor Shit

[Dialog Effects] | New addition :]

- Regular Effects (more to come, probably, maybe?)
[Shake] - this shakes the entire dialog even if you use [/Shake] and I cant figure out why D:

- Color Effects
[Red]SampleTextHere[/Red]
[Blue]SampleTextHere[/Blue]
[Green]SampleTextHere[/Green]
[Yellow]MoreSampleTextHere[/Yellow]
[Orange]EvenMoreSampleTextHere[/Orange]
[Purple]LotsOfSampleTextHere[/Purple]
[Brown]BunchOfSampleTextOverHere[/Brown]
[StaticRed]WholeLotHereToo[/StaticRed]
[StaticBlue]SoMuchSampleText[/StaticBlue]
[StaticYellow]TooMuchSampleText[/StaticYellow]
[StaticGreen]WhoTheHellOrderedSoMuchSampleText[/StaticGreen]
[StaticOrange]ImOverDosingOnSampleText[StaticOrange]
[StaticBrown]WhoTheHellWouldEvenUseBrownTextAnyways[StaticBrown]
[StaticPurple]SampleText[/StaticPurple]

- Examples of use:
[Red]This Is Red Text[Blue]And This Is Blue Text[/Blue]And Now We're back to red[/Red]
[Shake][Red]PretendTheresAngryShakyWordsHere[/Red]


[HealthRestore]
- RestoreHealth, Regenerates full health.
- RestoreSetHealth, Regenerates whatever you set the [Health Regen Amount] to be.
- RestoreQuarterHealth, Regenerates a quarter of Hp.
- RestoreHalfHealth, Regenerates half of it's Hp.

[ToggleInvinciblity]
- When Signal recieved, Toggle Invincibility.

[ExecutionTimer]
- UseRandomWaitingTime, Toggles if timer uses random time instead.
- MinWaitingTime, Minium amount of time that needs to pass before eligible to send signal.
- MaxWaitingTime, Maximum amount of time that can pass before sending signal.

[ZColors]
- Zombies & Humans can be painted into different colors, Spawnpoints also have this option incase you want a infinite horde of magenta for some reason.
- Zombies have TurnColor recievers, recieving a TurnColor signal will change into the color graudually using the specified ChangeColorTime.
- Static zombies will have dulled versions of their ZColor.

[Kill Reciever]
- When signal recieved, kills the zombie.
- RecieverDamageType, when signal recieved, zombie is killed with specified damage type.

[Vip]
- You can now give zombies the VIP treatment they've always deserved.

[One Way Colliders]
- Has active/inactive/toggle recievers now.

[Extended LevelSize]
- Level Width is extended to 5000. Unfortunately to achieve this, the game wont let you get a height above 250. 
If you know what your doing and edit the LVL file itself you can increase the height that way.
Alternatively if you don't know what your doing, save a copy of the LVL beforehand. (i dont wanna be responsible for you bricking the file somehow)

[Traps]
- Trap Mode, Kill or Damage options.
- Kill Delay, Self explanitory.
- Damage, Self explanitory.
- Damage Rate, How many damage is dealt per Ingame Second.
- Damage Type, Also self explanitory.

[Patroler]
- You can place Waypoints ontop of other Waypoints










